cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with the application of computer vision in agriculture, specifically in semantic segmentation of aerial farmland images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of image datasets and annotation also suggests the possibility of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes an effective model for aerial agricultural pattern recognition, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
